# CountDown App Development Guide

## Development Setup
1. Clone the repository
2. Install Xcode 15.0 or later
3. Install Firebase CLI for web deployment
4. Set up Firebase project and add configuration files

## Project Structure
- `countDown/` - iOS app source code
- `LP/` - Landing page files
- `Tests/` - Unit and UI tests
- `fastlane/` - CI/CD configuration

## Key Development Guidelines

### iOS App
- Use SwiftUI for UI components
- Follow MVVM architecture
- Use ComposableArchitecture for state management
- Maintain iOS 17.0+ compatibility
- Follow Apple's Human Interface Guidelines

### Landing Page
- Keep HTML/CSS in the `LP` directory
- Maintain responsive design
- Support both Japanese and English
- Follow web accessibility guidelines

### Firebase Integration
- Use Firebase Hosting for web deployment
- Implement Firebase Authentication
- Use Firestore for data storage
- Configure Firebase Analytics

### Testing
- Write unit tests for business logic
- Include UI tests for critical flows
- Test on multiple iOS versions
- Verify web compatibility

### Deployment
- Use fastlane for iOS deployment
- Deploy web updates via Firebase
- Maintain version control
- Follow semantic versioning

### Documentation
- Keep README.md updated
- Document major changes
- Maintain inline code comments
- Update App Store description
